Euro Falls For Third Day Against Dollar; Slipping to Almost Two-Week Low

-- B y   G a r t h   T h e u n i s s e n
-- 
2011-09-01T07:20:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/euro-falls-for-third-day-against-dollar-slipping-to-almost-two-week-low.html
The euro weakened against the dollar
for a third consecutive day, falling to an almost two-week low.  The 17-nation shared currency declined as much as 0.4
percent to $1.4314, the weakest intraday level since Aug. 19,
before trading at $1.4323 as of 8:19 a.m. in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Garth Theunissen in London at 
 gtheunissen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
